    <p>
    <strong>The 2009 International CES: Final Checklist</strong><br> by Dan Cole</p>
    <p>Continued from <a href="/exhibitors/newsletter/dec08.asp">first page</a>.</p>
    <SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Register your staff. It’s a simple task, but also one that exhibitors dread the most: badge ordering. This task becomes even more cumbersome when coupled with the need to collect and distribute those badges onsite. Do yourself a favor and submit your badge orders before December 11th. After this date, you will no longer be able to receive them in the mail prior to CES.<BR><BR>Confirm your target move-in date. Adherence to the CES target move-in schedule is vital to a smooth and efficient move-in process. Be sure to check the online exhibitor manual and confirm your company’s move-in (and move out) dates.&nbsp; Requests for target move-in changes must be submitted in writing to <A href="mailto:CESfreight@ges.com">CESfreight@ges.com</A> and are approved or denied on a case by case basis.&nbsp; Additional charges may apply.<BR><BR>Book meeting rooms, hospitality suites and press conference slots. If you require official CES space for closed-door meetings and hospitality, there is still a limited amount of inventory at the Venetian and Hilton suites, as well as meeting rooms in CES Meeting Place. Two-hour press conference slots are also still available for Thursday, January 8 and Friday, January 9 and can be secured by contacting Allison Carney with CES Communications at <A href="mailto:acarney@ce.org">acarney@ce.org</A>. <BR><BR>Secure last minute hotel rooms. Rooms and good rates at official CES hotels are still available. Some properties like Planet Hollywood, Trump International, Mandalay Bay, Luxor and Monte Carlo have recently reduced their rates as well. <BR><BR>Get some rest - CES is less than 30 days away, believe it or not! <BR>
